The paper deals with computational geometry and data structures, which are the main topics of cs.CG and cs.DS. The paper also involves algorithms for range searching and dominance reporting, which are relevant to cs.DM and cs.DC. Finally, the paper presents improved bounds for orthogonal range reporting in higher dimensions, which is related to cs.CC.
